Governorship candidate of the National Rescue Movement, NRM in Adamawa State, Alhaji Aliyu Maina, is dead. The National Publicity Secretary of NRM, Olusola Afuye who confirmed the incident said, “Aliyu Maina has been buried.” “According to the statement from the family, the late Alhaji Abba Maina died on Wednesday, January 25 at his residence in Federal Capital Territory, Abuja after a brief illness. “He has been buried according to Muslim rites. We pray to almighty Allah to protect his family and all his loved ones.” This is coming a few days after the gubernatorial candidate of the PDP in Abia state, Professor Ikonne was announced dead just weeks before the gubernatorial election.  As political activities gather momentum ahead of 2023 general elections, a presidential hopeful under the platform of the National Rescue Movement, NRM, Okwudili Nwa-Anyajike, weekend, assured Nigerians of 12 million jobs in two years if elected president In "News" One of the registered political parties in Nigeria, the National Rescue Movement  ( NRM), has thrown its weight behind the All Progressives Congress  (APC ), in Sokoto State , according to its  State Chairman, Alhaji Sabo Muhammad. In "News" By Gabriel Enogholase AHEAD of Edo State September 19 governorship election, National Rescue Movement, NRM, has sent a strong message to Peoples Democratic Party, PDP; its candidate, Godwin Obaseki and the opposition All Progressives Congress, APC, governorship candidate, Pastor Osagie Ize-Iyamu, that their time in power is over. In a… In "News"